    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 6,
      "text": "Our technique can be ported to other neural, multi-task setups with a strong dependence between tasks (e.g. where a model must learn to perform some task before attempting to learn one or more dependent tasks jointly).",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 7,
      "text": "For example, we have already begun porting this scheme to a neural cross-lingual summarization project of ours.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "Entity pre-training accounted for a 0.63% increase in our ablation experiment.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 9,
      "text": "On the CoNLL04 test set, it accounts for a 1.26% boost in performance, which is large relative to historic improvement on this corpus [1].",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 10,
      "text": "- As opposed to previous models (e.g. [2], [3]) we were able to drop all recurrent architectures, which reduced training times substantially.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 11,
      "text": "Our work is one of the first architectures for joint NER and RE to do this.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 12,
      "text": "Because previous papers do not report their training times, we contacted the authors of a comparable method [4] for their training times and found that our method converged between 3-35X times faster for the ACE04, ADE, and CoNLL04 corpora (keeping in mind that we did not train on the same hardware).",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 13,
      "text": "The large range in our estimate is because [4] trained for a wide range (60-200) of epochs.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 14,
      "text": "Our model serves as a strong baseline for future studies on joint NER and RE architectures and provides guidance on how to best integrate a pre-trained language model into such an architecture.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 15,
      "text": "For the ADE corpus in particular, we advance SOTA RE performance by >10%, which is substantially larger than improvements have been historically [5].",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
          5
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "SJlvvnJkcB",
      "rebuttal_id": "ryeNd3WQsr",
      "sentence_index": 16,
      "text": "It is also complementary to [6] (published in ACL this year), by demonstrating similar performance without the need for templated queries, which, as pointed out in our introduction, may become a limiting factor where domain expertise is required to craft such questions (e.g., for biomedical or clinical corpora).",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          4,
